<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             xmlns:unicode="clr-namespace:Avalonia.Media.TextFormatting.Unicode;assembly=Avalonia.Visuals"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="400" d:DesignHeight="400"
             x:Class="VRCLinuxAssistant.Pages.Intro">
    <Grid HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Width="1000" Height="400"
          RowDefinitions="auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto,auto">

        <TextBlock
            Margin="0"
            HorizontalAlignment="Left"
            VerticalAlignment="Center"
            FontSize="48"
            Text="Welcome to VRChat Linux Assistant" />
        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="1"
            Margin="0"
            FontSize="28"
            FontWeight="Bold"
            Text="Please read this page entirely and carefully" />
        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="2"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            By using this program attest to have read and agree to the following terms:
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="3"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            VRChat EXPLICITLY forbids modding the game client in their Terms of Service. This means:
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="4"
            Margin="15,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            Modding the client CAN lead to bans. Mods available via this installer are manually checked to minimize the chance of that happening, but THE RISK IS ALWAYS THERE.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="5"
            Margin="15,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            Mods WILL BREAK every update. This is normal, and NOT VRChat's fault.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="6"
            Margin="15,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            Mods WILL cause bugs and performance issues. This is NOT VRChat's fault.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="7"
            Margin="15,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            Mods are made for FREE by people in their FREE TIME Please be patient and understanding.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="8"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            DO NOT complain to VRChat Team because mods broke. This is NOT VRChat's fault. They are not trying to kill mods. Probably.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="9"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            If you want to report an issue with the game to VRChat Team, MAKE SURE THE ISSUE IS NOT CAUSED BY MODS To do so, remove all mods and/or MelonLoader and check if the issue still happens.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="10"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            "If I keep seeing people complain to the devs because mods broke, I will personally kill mods with a rusty spoon" - Knah, 2021
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock
            Grid.Row="11"
            Margin="0,5"
            FontSize="16"
            TextWrapping="Wrap"
            Text="Feel free to join the VRChat Modding group">
        </TextBlock>

        <StackPanel
            Grid.Row="12"
            Margin="10"
            HorizontalAlignment="Center"
            VerticalAlignment="Center"
            Orientation="Horizontal">
            <Button
                Name="Agree"
                Height="35"
                Margin="0,0,10,0"
                Padding="20,0,20,0"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Click="Agree_OnClick">
            <TextBlock
                    HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                    VerticalAlignment="Center"
                    FontSize="18"
                    Text="Agree" />
            </Button>
            <Button
                Name="Disagree"
                Height="35"
                Margin="10,0,0,0"
                Padding="20,0,20,0"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Click="Disagree_OnClick">
                <TextBlock
                    HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                    VerticalAlignment="Center"
                    FontSize="18"
                    Text="Disagree" />
            </Button>
        </StackPanel>
    </Grid>
</UserControl>
